Annotation.note:
A family of systems with symmetry group $C_3$ and common zero
$(1,1,1)$ with $m&gt;n\geq p$. 

The ideal generated by these polynomials has dimension 0 and
multiplicity $m^3$, since the polynomials form a deglex. Gr\&quot;obner
basis.

It can be generated by the following code:
\begin{verbatim}
#requires System=Maple
polys:=[
  x^m + y^n + z^p - 3,
  x^p + y^m + z^n - 3,
  x^n + y^p + z^m - 3];

vars:=[x,y,z];
\end{verbatim}

\begin{keywords}
discrete symmetries
\end{keywords}
